com.randallscharpf.java.jmorsecoding.base.symbolsets

Interface MorseSymbolSet

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ExtendedInternationalSymbolSet, InternationalSymbolSet, SymbolSetBase

    public interface MorseSymbolSet
    A translator from written characters and prosigns to dashes and dots. Each character or prosign is a "symbol" which, in Morse Code form, is a minimum meaningful unit that can be played.
    Since:
    1.0

    • Method Detail

      • getPlayableForString

        PlayableMorseUnit getPlayableForString(java.lang.String str)
        Returns a unit that plays the each of the characters in the given string in order, with proper separation. The string is terminated with a word gap so that it becomes a discrete message, unless the end of the provided string is whitespace.
        Parameters:
        str - the set of characters to compose the returned unit
        Returns:
        a gap-terminated PlayableMorseUnit for the input string
        Since:
        1.0

      • getPlayableForProsign

        PlayableMorseUnit getPlayableForProsign(java.lang.String prosignName)
        Returns a unit that plays a prosign. The prosign is followed by a word gap. The input string and prosign name (as listed in getAvailableProsigns() must be approximately the same, but the choice of comparison function is left open to implementers. A good choice for implementers is to compare the strings in lowercase, and users of this function should prefer to provide as parameter the exact string that appears in the list of available prosigns.
        Parameters:
        prosignName - a string giving the action represented by the prosign
        Returns:
        a gap-terminated PlayableMorseUnit for the requested prosign
        Since:
        1.0

      • getAvailableProsigns

        java.lang.String[] getAvailableProsigns()
        Gives the names of the prosigns registered as symbols in this set. The name of a prosign is typically related to the action it performs in communication or the written symbol used in transcripts of conversations to indicate that the prosign was sent. The names in this array must be such that calling getPlayableForProsign(java.lang.String) on any str that is an element of this array will give a valid PlayableMorseUnit and not instead throw an error.
        Returns:
        an array of the names of all prosigns supported by this symbol set
        Since:
        1.0
